<div class="main">
        
        <div class="stage_title container">
            <h3>Foreclosure Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="stage_info">
            
            <div class="stage_container c1">
                
                <h3>Foreclosure should only be considered as a last resort and should not be initiated until all Loss 
                Mitigation Options have been exhausted. When foreclosure cannot be avoided, it must be initiated prompty 
                to minimize losses to both the Lender and yourself. </h3>
                

            </div>

            <div class="stage_container c2">
                
                <h3>What will happen now ?</h3>
                <div>If you have not paid the mortgage, the bank will start contacting you to know when you can pay it. If you have fallen behind 1 to 2 months in payment, the bank will tell you that they will start the foreclosure process for your home.</div>

            </div>

            <div class="stage_container c3">
                
                <h3>What should I do ?</h3>
                <div>
                    You should consider consulting with a housing counselor to personally help you.<br>
                    Go to this website to find housing counselors near you: <a class="color_link" target="_blank" href="http://www.consumerfinance.gov/find-a-housing-counselor/">Consumer Financial Protection Bureau</a>
                </div>
            
            </div>

            <div class="stage_container c4">
                
                <h3>Can I do this on my own, without paying?</h3>
                <div>Yes, there a many housing counselors nearby that can assist you. Sometimes seeking the guidance 
                from an expert is the best thing you can do. Although you can do it on your own, doesnâ€™t mean you 
                should.</div>
            
            </div>
            
            <div class="stage_container c5">
                
                <h3> Do I have to file bankruptcy</h3>
                <div> No, bankruptcy is not necessary and is only one part of your credit. It is still possible to maintain a good standing
                by keeping up with all other lines of credit.
                </div>
                
            <div class="stage_container c6">
                
                <h3> How long til I can buy a house again?</h3>
                <div> Banks and Lenders now typically like to see 5-7 years since the foreclosure was discharged. However, some government 
                loan agencies currently require only 3 years.  Depending upon the down payment, there may also be 
                programs available that require only 1-2 years after the foreclosure has been settled.
                </div>

        </div>
    
    </div>

